The paper discusses nonparametric modeling approaches for system identification and control, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of Gaussian process regression and its limitations are also discussed, which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
